<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 13 at 1:58PM EDT  by NWS Pittsburgh</headline>
<description>...AN AREA OF MODERATE TO HEAVY SNOW WILL AFFECT EASTERN
MERCER...VENANGO... NORTHEASTERN BUTLER...JEFFERSON...NORTHERN
ARMSTRONG...CLARION AND FOREST COUNTIES...
At 157 PM EDT, an area of heavy snow was located along a line
extending from 8 miles northwest of Franklin to near Punxsutawney.
Movement was northeast at 40 mph.
Locations impacted include...
Oil City, Grove City, Franklin, Clarion, Brookville, Marienville,
Knox, Rimersburg, Sugarcreek, Slippery Rock, Reynoldsville, and
Brockway.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 79 in Pennsylvania between mile markers 117 and 133.
Interstate 80 in Pennsylvania between mile markers 18 and 96.</description>
